WEBVTT

00:03:59.714 --> 00:04:01.282
when they lived together.

00:04:02.225 --> 00:04:06.385
And we interviewed
all the families of the residents

00:04:06.409 --> 00:04:10.102
about "what is important for your father,"
"what's important for your mother,"

00:04:10.126 --> 00:04:12.875
"what is their life like,"
"what do they want."

00:04:12.899 --> 00:04:17.144
And we found seven groups,
and we call them lifestyle groups.

00:04:17.709 --> 00:04:21.370
And for instance,
we found this formal lifestyle.

00:04:21.851 --> 00:04:23.077
In this lifestyle,

00:04:23.101 --> 00:04:26.522
people have a more formal way
of interacting with each other,

00:04:26.546 --> 00:04:27.839
a distant way.

00:04:27.863 --> 00:04:30.109
Their daily rhythm
starts later in the day,